The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal

 Saturday, March 05, 2005 

 BRIEFS

 Durgapur, March 4: Thirty-nine students of Asansol Polytechnic have been asked to vacate hostel following lewd conduct at the wedding of an institute employee. 

 The students, who went to the wedding on Wednesday drunk, made passes at women and allegedly turned violent when guests protested. 

 Burdwan: Three people were killed and many injured when a bus fell into a ditch here. Two of the dead were identified as Shyamaprasad Mallick, 45, a telephone exchange employee, and Rabi Dutta, 35. Many of the passengers were Madhyamik examinees. Some of them took the test from hospital.

 Behrampore: Joykrishan Purkayat, 28, was murdered inside a mental hospital here on Friday. The man from Canning, South 24-Parganas, was found with his throat slit and belly ripped open. A broken saline bottle and a cap worn by a fellow patient were nearby. Nazimuddin, whose cap it was, was arrested.

 Burdwan: Tumpa Ruidas, 7, was killed and probably raped before that by two boys of her locality ? one 22 and the other 14. Guests at a wedding at Jhijhira village first smelt foul when they saw blood on the shirts of Suresh Badyakar and Sourav Bauri.




